This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring May 7, 2015, as the National Day of Prayer. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of religious freedom and the ability to practice any faith without fear or discrimination. It recognizes prayer as an essential act of worship and a source of strength and guidance. The proclamation also acknowledges the challenges faced by religious communities around the world and expresses the United States' commitment to protecting religious freedom globally. The article concludes by inviting citizens to give thanks and pray for guidance, mercy, and protection as they seek a more just world.